article.headline: Charleston Southern 73, Stetson 64
article.story: CHARLESTON, S.C. -- Mathiang Muo scored 22 points and Kelvin Martin tallied a double-double, helping Charleston Southern rally for a 73-64 win over Stetson on Monday night. Martin scored 15 points and grabbed 10 rebounds for the Buccaneers (3-2), who also got 14 points from Arlon Harper. Stetson led 26-22 at the break, but Jeremy Sexton pulled Charleston Southern even at 32-all with a 3-pointer less than five minutes into the second half. The teams kept trading leads, with Joel Naburgs hitting a 3 to put Stetson back ahead 51-49 with 7:25 left. But Muo answered with a 3-pointer of his own, starting an 11-0 run for the Buccaneers. They wouldn't trail again, outscoring the Hatters 51-38 in the second half to seal the comeback win. Both teams grabbed 34 rebounds each, but Charleston Southern forced 26 turnovers. Aaron Graham led the Hatters (3-2) with 17 points.
